        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 8:30PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 830 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 5 miles west of Glenburn to 5 miles southwest
of Minot. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minot, Burlington, Surrey, Glenburn, Minot Air Force Base, and
Wolseth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
